<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
var b1 = Boolean(100);
var b2 = Boolean(3.14);
var b3 = Boolean(-15);
var b4 = Boolean("Hello");
var b5 = Boolean('false');
var b6 = Boolean(1 + 7 + 3.14);

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
"100 is " + b1 + "<br>" +
"3.14 is " + b2 + "<br>" +
"-15 is " + b3 + "<br>" +
"Any (not empty) string is " + b4 + "<br>" +
"Even the string 'false' is " + b5 + "<br>" +
"Any expression (except zero) is " + b6 + "<br>" +
"PJH"
</script>

</body>
</html>


*

// zero , minus zero , empty string , undefinded , null , false(false) , NaN (ex) 10 /"H") 
-> return false


*


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<p>Never create booleans as objects. PJH</p>
<p>Booleans and objects cannot be safely compared.</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
var x = false;         // x is a boolean
var y = new Boolean(false);  // y is an object
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = typeof x + "<br>" + typeof y;
</script>

</body>
</html>


*


